        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Lsp has 26 modules and treesitter has 11.\n\nIf you look you'll see there aren't a bunch of micro modules. Most of them are 100s LOC. Believe it or not, vim.diagnostic has had tonnes of feature creep.\n\nSome of the smaller modules were required to keep a hygienic dependency graph.\n\nI also believe not having a structure to begin with made the module very interconnected which lead it to being broken up so much to keep the dependency graph clean. It may be possible to consolidate some of this with deeper refactors.\n\n> If the diagnostic module is too big, find the actual big topics that should be split, rather than splitting into the maximum granularity.\n\nPlease give a more concrete proposal. Look at the code first at review which parts you don't want split. To me it made sense.",
