        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It does look pretty good. And it looks like this allow `_defer_require()` which might be a benefit (worth mentioning in commit message).\r\n\r\n- I think the `handlers/*` could be in one `_handlers.lua`. \r\n- Some core things like `_list.lua` and `_shared.lua` could be in `diagnostic.lua`, unless that's the \"clean dep graph\" issue you mentioned. \r\n\r\nMainly want to avoid hyper-granularity, which is extremely common cargo-cult habit in javascript/typescript world. This PR isn't that, but want to align on future expectations.",
