        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`_shared.lua` is basically the `util.lua` of Lsp, and is stuff used in many places, that needs to be separate unless we make an exception to dep graph hygiene. `list.lua` can be moved back.\n\nI can probably make a single `handlers.lua`, but unlike LSP handlers, each handler here is more like a class with several methods which is why I chose to break it up more. Personally I don't like having multiple class definitions like that in a single file as it makes grepping a bit of a pain as you hit each version, e.g. when searching for the `show` method. Not a massive deal. I'll look into it.",
